<br>
Does anyone know of some relatively easy to obtain (for a 45 Druid) magic resist gear?  I have a shiny brass shield on my Bard that I can borrow, but other than that I think I've got zilch.<br>
<br>
Thanks for your suggestions!<br>
<br>
Aerynn<br>
- 45 Wood Elf Druid <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukatlynel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Katlynel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/11/01 1:25:37 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.asianavenue.com/indiegrrl/faedrake.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need help with Magic Resistance</span><hr size=1> platinum wolf's eye agate necklace 10svmagic<br>
splitpaw hide mask 5svmagic<br>
spectral shroud (back slot) 5svmagic<br>
sceptre of flame 5svmagic<br>
jewelcrafted MR bracers, I forget, shouldn't be too expensive <p><font face="Verdana, Arial" size="2">
Katlynel Wolfcaller
<BR>57 Preserver, <a href="http://www.aradani.com/warcouncil">The War Council</a>, Saryrn
</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uquelm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quelm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/11/01 1:43:50 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need help with Magic Resistance</span><hr size=1> also check out:<br>
<br>
Crested Mistmoore Shield<br>
Hollowed Bone Bracers<br>
<br>
-Quelm <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubetina.showPublicProfile?language=EN>betina</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/11/01 4:22:33 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.mindspring.com/~mhuang/eq/pics/betina-new.gif height=120 width=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need help with Magic Resistance</span><hr size=1> I would not worry too much about Magic Resistance for Plane of Hate. Unless you are planning on going after the 2nd Floor mobs (where they will nuke you as well as Grav Flux you) or after Innoruuk himself, your primary worry should be your AC/hitpoints. <br>
<br>
A druid's role in Hate basically consists of playing either a) healer/buffer or b) nuker/snarer. <br>
<br>
Both of these roles have a very good chance of getting you on the mob's hate list, also the mobs will summon you and hit for 125-150 per pop.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utetriancorbec.showPublicProfile?language=EN>tetrian corbec</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/11/01 7:06:52 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need help with Magic Resistance</span><hr size=1> 2x platinium Jacinth rings for pure magic ressist (13mr) goes for around 1k pp or so each, maybe a little more.<br>
<br>
Or (this is the best all round)2x platinium Diamond rings.(7vs mr cr fr dr pr) goes for around 1.5 - 2k each.<br>
<br>
Also, 2 blue diamond bracers would rock pretty bad, but they are pretty expensive, aprox 5k each on brell.<br>
<br>
dont worry too much about ressists on plane of hate, but a pair of diamond rings would be a good investment,  no matter how you plan your eq future. ( its most likely gonna include some raids) =)<br>
<br>
Good luck.<br>
<br>
Tet. <p><img src=http://www.facelink.com/edit/raw/rawimage/71/1522171.bmp>
